- Unary
  - client send one request & server responds with a response
  
- Server Streaming
  - enabled by HTTP2
  - clients send one request & server returns one or more responses
  - use cases where where clients wants to get updated values
  
- Client streaming
  - Client sends one or more reuqests & server responds with one response
  - e.g. uploading of info
  
- Bi directional streaming
  - client send multiple requests & server can send multiple responses
  - After the first request, the responses could arrive in any order you decide.
    - You can get response per request or per two requests etc.
